            family: "invariant_stress",
            proposed: "Algebraic monotonicity claim: sigma(n) > sigma(n−1) holds at primes (sigma jumps to n+1) but FAILS at composites (e.g. sigma(6)=12 > sigma(7)=8 is FALSE — wait, 12 > 8 IS true). Counter: sigma(6)=12 > sigma(5)=6 yes, sigma(6)=12 > sigma(7)=8 yes — both directions monotone-ish. Real hypothesis: sigma is non-monotone since sigma is multiplicative-irregular. Candidate: prove sigma(n) ≥ n+1 for n>1, equality iff prime.",
